msgid "Statistics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:8 b6d9785a3bc944c08707e9cbb6975097
msgid "Estimated Qubes OS userbase graph"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:12 6dc6083f76b84c9d97100f3493830d14
msgid "FAQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:16 289dc83811a14259bc049c4b82656939
msgid "How often is this graph updated?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:19 7e99d84c53044e1985b85e2fb35f8650
msgid "Daily."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:22 963ab68607d24a68994313f0aca97528
msgid "Why is the bar for the current month so low?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:25 3b396c7aba554e728248fb552b1ee96d
msgid ""
"Since the graph is updated daily, the bar for the current month will be "
"very low at the start of the month and rise gradually until the end of "
"the month."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:28 eaf3cf17ce524dd0be41fd6f2e437374
msgid "How is the userbase estimated?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:31 c9e9e7ad01554f9aa6f66510493149a0
msgid ""
"We simply count the number of unique IPv4 addresses that connect to the "
"Qubes update servers each month (except for Tor connections; see `below "
"<#how-are-tor-users-counted>`__). (**Note:** Users who have manually "
"configured their systems to bypass the metalink and connect directly to a"
" mirror are not counted.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:34 09f70518c0614383b40cb36f87dcf22c
msgid "How are Tor users counted?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:37 50f129e998bf411ebcffd157751c6c23
msgid ""
"We estimate the number of Tor users as a proportion of the total number "
"of *requests* from Tor exit nodes on the assumption that the proportion "
"of users to requests is roughly the same for both clearnet and Tor users."
" To be precise, the formula is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:45 9568de4054894cf397f3b3a9617f1386
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:47 9e85a8eebf3544758fb992a50874858e
msgid ""
"``tor_users`` is the estimated number of Qubes users who download updates"
" via Tor each month."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:49 59223238cc6a4de292f56b217b252677
msgid ""
"``tor_requests`` is the total number of requests the Qubes update servers"
" receive from Tor exit nodes each month."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:51 1226815df76a4174b29c66d2351d3d5e
msgid ""
"``plain_users`` is the number of unique clearnet IPv4 addresses that "
"connect to the Qubes update servers each month."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:53 7505fdfa8a424a9eb7fef46e00b621c8
msgid ""
"``plain_requests`` is the total number of requests the Qubes update "
"servers receive from clearnet IPv4 addresses each month."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:57 ea69029ccb5a45c0991f9aaa21d74847
msgid ""
"We cross-reference the list of connecting IP addresses with `TorDNSEL’s "
"exit lists <https://metrics.torproject.org/collector.html#type-"
"tordnsel>`__ in order to distinguish Tor and clearnet IPs and requests. "
"For this purpose, we count an IP address as belonging to a Tor exit node "
"if there was a Tor exit node active for that address within the 24-hour "
"periods before or after it connected to the Qubes update servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:60 bcfd66bc84e644a385afc890448826af
msgid "What kinds of data do you collect about Qubes users?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:63 b2b09ed406cf44c5b981e130f6c3edb8
msgid "Please see our :doc:`Privacy Policy </introduction/privacy>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:66 032ddfdb13b944e0b1e6357b92f616d6
msgid "Where can I find the raw data and source code?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/statistics.rst:69 4ca38a31c3004b76bad10c799a5e4569
msgid ""
"The raw data is available `here <https://tools.qubes-"
"os.org/counter/stats.json>`__. (This does not include any personally-"
"identifying user data.) Please note that the format of this data is not "
"documented and may change any time if the developers feel the need to "
"include something else. The source code is available `here "
"<https://github.com/woju/qubes-stats>`__."
msgstr ""

